So there are 8 long words for, 56 amount. We can now convert the ratio 8/56 into percent. We find the long word percent, for us we found is 14.285. or which is rounded off = 14.

We now have A (56 words), B (3 sentences), and O (14% of long words). Next, we will find LIX as follows:

LIX = (O + (100 * A / B))

